The 2019 Digital Marketing Conference will take place on 13 November 2019 at The Venue in Melrose Arch. The conference is aimed at marketing professionals and business owners who want to learn more about digital marketing. Topics which will be covered include content marketing, campaign targeting and optimisation, PR in the digital age, lead generation, and social media marketing. The conference will feature top speakers, including Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou, brand communication specialist Musa Kalenga and MyBroadband’s Kevin Lancaster. Registrations for the 2019 Digital Marketing Conference are open and you can register here: Please note that only 50 early-bird tickets are available for the event at this discounted price, and these seats will be allocated on a first-come-first-served basis.